# If postfix is included here then netdata tries to run a postfix server, which
# then misinteracts with the system's *actual* postfix instance (presumably
# because postfix service sockets exist in both containers via bind-mounts?)
#
# 1.x.x:
#net-analyzer/netdata			 aclk ap apcups bind bpf cloud +compression cups +dbengine dhcp dovecot +go ipmi +jsonc lxc mongodb mysql nfacct nginx nodejs nvme podman postfix postgres prometheus +python qos sensors smart systemd tor xen
# 2.x.x:
#net-analyzer/netdata			 ap apcups -beanstalkd bind bpf +compression cups +dashboard +dbengine dhcp dovecot +go ipmi +jsonc lto lxc mongodb mysql nfacct nginx nodejs nvme podman postfix postgres prometheus +python qos sensors smart snmp systemd tor xen
#
